{"timestep": 4, "agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell", "description": "Run a shell command in the task work_dir (bash -lc).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"command": {"description": "Shell command string passed to `bash -lc`.", "title": "Command", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["command"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "read_text_file", "description": "Read a UTF-8 text file relative to work_dir.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_text_file", "description": "Write text to a path under work_dir (creates parent dirs).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"relative_path": {"description": "Path under the workspace (not absolute).", "title": "Relative Path", "type": "string"}, "content": {"description": "Full file body to write as UTF-8 text.", "title": "Content", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["relative_path", "content"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_rscript", "description": "Run inline R code via Rscript -e (single line safe for agents).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"code": {"description": "R expression passed as the argument to `Rscript -e`.", "title": "Code", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["code"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "list_workdir", "description": "List workspace as JSON (bounded depth).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": []}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_plan", "description": "Persist a markdown plan to `workspace/.plan.md` (overwrite on rewrite).\n\nUse this at the start of a task and whenever the plan needs revision. The\nplan is not shown automatically on later steps; call check_progress to see\nthe current plan excerpt alongside deliverable state.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_to_tibble`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_to_tibble\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `late`, difficulty: `3`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given a methylKit united object at `input/mk_united.rds`. Convert it into\na long tibble with columns `(chr, start, end, strand, metric, value, sample)` using\n`pivot_longer` on the `coverage*`/`numCs*` columns, and save it to\n`output/df_mku.rds`. Then pivot wide on `metric`, compute `mCpG = numCs / coverage`,\ngroup by `(sample, chr)`, and write the mean mCpG table to `output/mean_mcpg.tsv`\nusing `readr::write_tsv` with columns `sample, chr, mean_mCpG`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mean_mcpg.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_db\": {\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleA.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleA.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleA.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleA.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleB.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleB.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleB.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleB.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleC.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleC.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleC.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleC.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleD.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleD.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleD.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleD.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"mk_united.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_united.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_iMFCzvpG92Za6SbEFoY4iuP4", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit object from the RDS file located at `input/mk_united.rds`.\\n2. Convert the methylKit object into a long tibble format using `pivot_longer` on columns starting with `coverage` and `numCs`.\\n3. Save the long tibble to `output/df_mku.rds`.\\n4. Pivot the long tibble to a wide format and calculate the methylation percentage (mCpG) as `numCs / coverage`.\\n5. Compute the mean mCpG for each combination of sample and chromosome.\\n6. Save the mean mCpG table to `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` using `readr::write_tsv`.\\n7. Verify the existence of `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (604 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_iMFCzvpG92Za6SbEFoY4iuP4"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_2UW58Db3u4aC7PfLzUY6UGOG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(readr)\\n\\n# Load the methylKit object\\nmethylBase <- readRDS('input/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Convert to a data frame and pivot longer\\ndf_long <- methylBase %>%\\n  as.data.frame() %>%\\n  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with('coverage') | starts_with('numCs'),\\n               names_to = 'metric',\\n               values_to = 'value')\\n\\n# Save the long format tibble\\nsaveRDS(df_long, 'output/df_mku.rds')\\n\\n# Pivot wider and calculate mCpG\\ndf_wide <- df_long %>%\\n  pivot_wider(names_from = metric, values_from = value) %>%\\n  mutate(mCpG = numCs / coverage)\\n\\n# Calculate mean mCpG per sample and chromosome\\nmean_mcpg <- df_wide %>%\\n  group_by(sample, chr) %>%\\n  summarize(mean_mCpG = mean(mCpG, na.rm = TRUE))\\n\\n# Write the result to a TSV file\\nwrite_tsv(mean_mcpg, 'output/mean_mcpg.tsv')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var, xtabs\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    anyDuplicated, aperm, append, as.data.frame, basename, cbind,\n    colnames, dirname, do.call, duplicated, eval, evalq, Filter, Find,\n    get, grep, grepl, is.unsorted, lapply, Map, mapply, match, mget,\n    order, paste, pmax, pmax.int, pmin, pmin.int, Position, rank,\n    rbind, Reduce, rownames, sapply, saveRDS, table, tapply, unique,\n    unsplit, which.max, which.min\n\nLoading required package: S4Vectors\n\nAttaching package: \u2018S4Vectors\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:utils\u2019:\n\n    findMatches\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    expand.grid, I, unname\n\nLoading required package: IRanges\nLoading required package: GenomeInfoDb\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:methylKit\u2019:\n\n    select\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:GenomicRanges\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, union\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:GenomeInfoDb\u2019:\n\n    intersect\n\nThe following objects are mas